- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses information-theoretic tools such as self-normalized martingale difference terms to bound identification error. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the finite time error bounds for estimating LTI systems, which involves numerical analysis techniques. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): Although not the main focus of the paper, the method of least squares is a fundamental algorithm in data analysis and could potentially fall under this category.
